cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper focuses on object detection tasks on aerial images using unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) with mounted cameras. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also emphasizes the differences between natural and aerial images in the context of object detection task, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of object detection algorithms, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a multi-purpose aerial dataset, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of the dataset in filling the gap between computer vision and robotics, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
